title: Women perform worse in CPR
summary: Does it matter whether a man or a woman carries out CPR? Researchers have shown that female resuscitation teams performed cardiopulmonary resuscitation less efficiently than their male counterparts. The study suggests that there is a need for action in the training of young female physicians.
